Durban - Police are still searching for the suspect who shot dead a Pietermaritzburg man in his driveway and injured a teenager. According to Lietenant Colonel Thulani Zwane on August 30 at 7amÂ a 47-year-old man was leaving his premises at Indus Road in Copesville when an unknown man opened fire towards his vehicle. "He sustained multiple gunshot wounds on the body and was certified dead at the scene," said Zwane. He said a 15-year-old passer-by was shot in the back and was taken to hospital for medical attention. "Charges of murder and attempted murder will be opened at Mountain Rise police station for investigation." "According to Russel Meiring from ER24 when paramedics arrived on scene they quickly assessed the man and found that he showed no signs of life, having sustained a gunshot wound to his head. "Unfortunately, nothing could be done for him and he was declared dead on scene." POST